# Project MD Reconstructor

Also read:
- `../../references/project-template.md`
- `../../references/frontend-tech-template.md`
- `../../references/backend-tech-template.md`
- `../../references/scanning-rules.md`

Goal:
- classify the current repository as frontend, backend, full-stack, or unclear before writing anything
- always create or update `docs/project.md`
- only create or update `docs/project-frontend-tech.md` for frontend or full-stack repositories
- only create or update `docs/project-backend-tech.md` for backend or full-stack repositories
- explicitly document reusable building blocks and extension points so future work reuses existing structures
- keep frontend and backend technical details in separate files
- if the project type is unclear, update only `docs/project.md` and list missing evidence
- prefer evidence-backed statements and mark unclear conclusions as inferred or unknown
